sql:
SELECT type_of_leave, COUNT(*) AS total_requests
FROM time_off
GROUP BY type_of_leave;

SELECT organizer_name, department
FROM organizers
ORDER BY department, organizer_name;

SELECT event_type_name
FROM event_types
WHERE LENGTH(RTRIM(event_type_name)) = (
  SELECT MAX(LENGTH(RTRIM(event_type_name)))
  FROM event_types
);

external_knowledge:
- Event attendees are employees of the organization; 
- Event organizers are also employees with specific roles and permissions; 
- Event attendance status indicates whether an attendee has attended, been absent, or has a pending status; 
- Running total of attendance statuses implies calculating the cumulative count of attendance statuses for each event over time.
